Seriously considering relocating to Oceanside, CA just for the food by @erisfoodco 
The owner Scott is a culinary genius, although he will humbly say he sees himself as a “culinary artist”. The menu has so many incredible options, whatever you choose know that you will be 
getting the very best in house vegan food ever! 
Whether you are a local or visiting the area you need to put this place on your list of places to eat!
We noticed that Scott is a Ramones fan, and upon speaking with him learned that he is a huge CJ Ramone and Me First and the Gimmie Gimmes fan. Scott extended an invitation to @theecjramone to come in and enjoy a free meal. I recommend you take Scott up on the offer CJ, I promise it’s worth the drive! 

#theecjramone #erisfoodco #oceansidecalifornia #bestveganeats #bestveganfood

Introducing our newest pack member Drako! 
He is a Shilo Shepherd, although we think he maybe part moose as his ears look a lot like antlers. He is estimated to weigh 120 - 150lbs when fully grown.
He is super sweet, funny, and currently very clumsy. His giant paws are often in his own way. 
Drako gets along great with all of the pups in our pack and he is the perfect addition to our family!

Crushing goals, raising the bar! DRAKO graduated STAR puppy class, and the same day took all 3 AKC Canine Good Citizen tests and passed them all. He also aced the AKC Trick Dog Novice test! 4 AKC Titles in one day, and the week before he earned 2 AKC Manners titles. I couldn’t be more impressed by this pup at 3 months old and only having been with me for 3 weeks, to earn 6 AKC Titles is quite the accomplishment! I can’t wait to see what he does next!  #puppytraining #smartpuppy #servicedogintrainingpuppy

Drako with the save! While on vacation my husband picked up breakfast at the hotel for us. He asked if it was nut free and was told it was. I sat down with my bowl and Drako alerted. I put my glasses on and saw the granola contained chopped almonds. This isn’t video of the actual event but I told my hubby to grab my phone so we could capture Drako alerting to the nuts in the food! I am severely allergic to tree nuts and had I eaten this I would have had a life threatening anaphylactic reaction! Great work by Drako!!! 🌰 🐾❤️ #herodog #drakotheshilo #servicedogtraining #workingdog #nutallergiesareserious

In loving memory of my precious brother Muggy. He passed peacefully at home on his own in my Momma’s arms yesterday surrounded by all of us, knowing how much he is loved. His little heart was so tired and Momma told him it was ok if he needed to go and he did. Forever in our hearts until we all meet again at the rainbow bridge. ❤️🐾🌈❤️

Dear friends, we are so thankful for your heartfelt words of support and for the flowers and cards you have sent during this difficult time. I received this beautiful bracelet engraved with Muggy’s name and a paw print, inside of the bracelet it says; “Once by my side, forever in my heart.” This gift came with no card, so I do not know who sent it. Please let me know if it was you. It is a very treasured piece that holds a special place in my heart. Thank you so very much.  Hug all of your beautiful fur babies tight. The world is such a better place having them in our lives. ❤️🐾🌈

When your Gigantic, Little Bro be trying to steal your thunder… Seriously though, great work helping keeping our Hoomom safe Drako I couldn’t ask for a better addition to our pack! #servicedoginprogress #servicedogintraining #workingdogsofig #servicedogpuppyintraing #shiloshepherd #shiloshepherdsofinstagram #MyShiloDrako

Bragging rights!!! Check out my Giant, Little Bro… 
Drako at 8 months entered his first Rally event. This handsome, goofy boy shocked us all by taking 3rd place! 
This sport is new to both him and my HooMom and they truly had no idea how this event was going to go, so she didn’t check them in as she worried neither of them were  prepared. She figured she would watch the event with him and see what she could learn and have him just observe and learn to settle in while in this type of setting. 
At the last minute she decided to go for it and give it a try. Somehow she managed to navigate the course and he focused that puppy brain of his, they worked together as a team and pulled it off. 
I have to say I’m so proud of this pup for always showing up when my Hoomom needs him and for also never hiding his silly side which always makes all of us smile. #shiloshepherd #cutepup #dogsports
